title: Jack Teixeira expected to plead guilty in documents leak case
description: The request comes almost a year after Teixeira was arrested and charged with the illegal retention and transmission of national defense information. He originally pleaded not guilty to the charges.

title: Judge skeptical of lawsuit brought by Elon Musk's X over hate speech research
description: The nonprofit sued by Elon Musk's X says the legal tactic is an attempt to silence criticism of the company. The Center for Countering Digital Hate published reports documenting hate speech on X.

title: Iowa basketball phenom Caitlin Clark plans to forgo next season and enter WNBA Draft
description: Caitlin Clark, who is on the verge of becoming the all-time NCAA scoring leader in college basketball, announced that she will leave the Hawkeyes after this season and turn pro.

title: Putin warns of nuclear war if NATO sends troops to Ukraine
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin issued explicit nuclear threats to the West, even as he assured Russians their country could both win the war in Ukraine and thrive economically.

title: Farms fuel global warming. Billions in tax dollars likely aren't helping - report
description: A new report finds some of the "climate-smart" agricultural practices that the USDA are subsidizing may not reduce emissions. It adds up to billions of taxpayer dollars.

title: 50 years ago, 'Blazing Saddles' broke wind — and box office expectations
description: Mel Brooks' satirical Western got mixed reviews when it opened in February 1974, but it became the year's biggest box office hit.

title: A timeline of allegations against Sean Combs
description: The rap mogul has been accused of sexual misconduct in five different civil suits since November 2023, dating back to the beginning of one of hip-hop's most influential careers.

title: My daughters sold Girl Scout Cookies. Here's what I learned in the Thin Mint trenches
description: There are no Wonka-like scenes of Tagalong rainbows and Do-si-do stools. But parents can be forgiven for feeling like Oompa Loompas — hardworking cogs in a well-oiled machine.

title: Yes, these 5 Oscar-nominated documentaries take on tough topics — watch them anyway
description: From war to injustice and religious extremism, the documentary finalists are thematically harrowing stories from around the world. Each is a triumph of storytelling and craft.

title: Gaza's death toll now exceeds 30,000. Here's why it's an incomplete count
description: Gaza's health ministry announced Thursday that 30,035 Palestinians have been killed in the war. A close look at how the ministry counts those killed reveals a system buckling under the weight of war.

title: How genetically modified pigs could end the shortage of organs for transplants
description: Scientists are optimistic that gene-edited animals could provide a new source of organs for transplantation. Pig organs modified to minimize rejection are now being tested in humans.

title: Virginia high school students take center stage for Black History Month celebration
description: High school students in Alexandria, Va., honor Black history with art, dance and theater.

title: Older US adults should get another COVID-19 shot, health officials recommend
description: The CDC said Americans 65 and older should get another dose of the updated vaccine that became available in September — if at least four months has passed since their last shot.
